      "lineNbr": 25,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-25T17:16:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "we might or we might not. The problem with exported_invocation_id is that it is not extensible / not future-proof: if we ever needs tags or realms, we will have to add exported_invocation_realm, exported_invocation_tags, parent_invocation_realms, parent_invocation_tags, which would be awkward. Why not make it future proof? For the consumer, it is the same number of characters they have to type: exported_invocation.id vs exported_invocation_id\n\nalso this is inconsistent with TestResult, so can be confusing/annoying to the users. Why not make it consistent?",
      "parentUuid": "b32f1cf2_e8be45ad",
      "range": {
