      "writtenOn": "2020-11-24T20:47:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Another downside of doing this this way and not sharding always is that we loose streaming support. There\u0027s potentially value in long running tests. I think it\u0027s fine, just have to be a conscious choice. In practice, having large blobs will make casual analysis much faster than a ton of LAG() OVER() statements that are hard to get right.\n\nNodir, any take?",
