      "writtenOn": "2020-11-25T17:16:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "note that we plan to export these rows not when artifact are being written, but when an invocation is finalized. This is because the set of included invocations is mutable, so an indirect artifact child can be excluded from an invocation after the artifact is written. This kind of precludes streaming.\n\nI am not sure I understood your point about large blobs. FWIU the intention here is to cut only artifacts that reach the limit, so blobs\u003c5MB will stay whole.",
